iguration options.</p>\n<p>Containers allow a developer to package up an application with all of the parts it needs, such as libraries and other dependencies, and ship it all out as one package.</p>\n<p>main Concepts to learn about Docker.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Docker Images</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Docker Images contain our application code + everything the app needs to run. e.g all the modules etc are inside the the image. (just remembering this line is all docker)\n</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Docker Containers.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Containers basically run Images inside them.\n</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Introduction to Containers and Docker","date":"November 22, 2018"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/introduction-to-containers-and-docker/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/exposing-your-app-in-kubernetes/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Exposing your app in Kubernetes"}},"next":null}}